Class GMeans

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Initialization

    public class GMeans
extends AbstractInitialization
    The Class KMeansPlusPlus initializes centroid cluster model like in Kmeans ++ algorithm. First centroid is randomly selected and other (K-1) centroids are initialized as follows:. Distances from every centroid to every example is calculated and an example with farthest distance from any centroid becomes new centroid. David Arthur , Sergei Vassilvitskii, k-means++: the advantages of careful seeding, Proceedings of the eighteenth annual ACM-SIAM symposium on Discrete algorithms, p.1027-1035, January 07-09, 2007, New Orleans, Louisiana
